==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hallowed
<hw>hallowed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>belonging to or derived from or
associated with a divine power; made holy. Opposite of
<ant>unholy</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>beatified, blessed
</stype>; <stype>blessed </stype>; <stype>consecrated, sacred,
sanctified </stype>] <see>Also See: <er>consecrated</er>,
<er>consecrate</er>, <er>sacred</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> holy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halloween</ent>⟦br⟧
